bitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Howel","type":"LAST","meanings":["The English form of the Welsh name Hywel."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Jevan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, originally a nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>jovene</i> ‘young’ (Latin <i>iuvenis</i>). Use as a given name has probably been influenced by its similarity in sound to   Evan ."],"variants":[{"name":"Jeavon","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jevon ."]},{"name":"Jeevan","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jevon ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jevan Ap Howel was born about 1357, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Howel ap Griffith, was 42 and his mother, Mrs Howel ap Griffith, was 31. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Jevan ap Howel."},"et":{"abt. 1357–":"umbes 1357–Surnud","1357–Male":"1357–Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1397–Male":"1397–Surnud","1317–Male":"1317–Surnud","1328–Female":"1328–Surnud","1357":"1357","abt. 1357":"umbes 1357","ABT 1397":"umbes 1397","1365":"1365","1397":"1397","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wales":"Wales","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn., Wls.":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt. 1357–":"noin 1357–Kuollut","1357–Male":"1357–Kuollut","1365–Female":"1365–Kuollut","1397–Male":"1397–Kuollut","1317–Male":"1317–Kuollut","1328–Female":"1328–Kuollut","1357":"1357","abt. 1357":"noin 1357","ABT 1397":"noin 1397","1365":"1365","1397":"1397","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wales":"Wales","of Glyn-Nedd